    {
      "id": 5,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 1,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 4,
      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "Getting in touch",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>Getting in touch<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ],
              "isBold": true
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "February, 2099<!$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ],
              "isBold": true
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::2>The shock of Mik"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s birthday night faded with each passing week. In its place was a sense that he had changed, saw things more clearly now. He had cautiously asked around if any of the other kids that had been at other checkpoints that night had gotten shit from the Secs. None had "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " the New Kendall brass seemed eager to move on, not keep the conversation alive. Nila had seen that with her mom, who wouldn’t talk about it at all."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Nila and he, on the other hand, had been doing a lot of talking. He"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’d told her again that he didn’t know if he would leave New Kendall, but she seemed to take it in stride. Something was brewing between them, he could feel that. He just didn’t know what yet. But he wanted to find out."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "That would have to wait. She was off with her mom, who insisted she accompany her to some Sec conference somewhere. All very hush, hush. So it was back with the old gang again this Friday night. First he"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’d have to go through the obligatory Dinner with the Folks routine."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Not that he hated his parents. Tiffany and Larry were alright, in their own way. Some of his parents friends were far worse. But not more annoying. T&L seemed to think that asking him a million questions was giving him a chance to express himself, to connect with them. The problem was that they only wanted to hear certain answers and it was exhausting trying to figure out what the right ones were."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Tonight they seemed concerned about his occupational choices."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I imagine the first pass on The List will be out soon,” Larry said, like he had just discovered something vital."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Three weeks,” Mik replied."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Any rumors about what’s going to be on it?” Tiffany asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“About a million,” Mik said. “The usual: rats for Sec, cannon fodder for Def, marketing, logistics, AI interfacers, eng software monkeys, etcetera. There’s a rumor they’re looking for people with non-English speaking skills.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Interesting,” Larry intoned. “Wonder what that’s about?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I hear there are problems in Asia,” Tiffany said. “My boss was called into a big meeting last week. Slowdown in production there, someone said.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They went on with office gossip for awhile, which was fine with him, as he knew nothing and cared less. But then they remembered their Mission in Life, raising a Good Citizen of New Kendall. The son who would make sure that they were taken care of when they could no longer contribute to the corporation."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, anyway, Mik, back to The List,” Larry said. “Anything got your eye so far?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I was thinking maybe AI interfacer,” he said, just to keep things going. “Soft eng is too deep "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " I got lost in that. Lucky to get Bs. But all that AI stuff doesn’t really work right most of the time and they need people to troubleshoot it, go in and see where the algos go wrong. Turns out I’m good at spotting what doesn’t belong.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Hmm, I guess that could be good,” Tiff said. “It seems a little boring.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Unlike all the other jobs, he thought. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I suppose. Maybe boring is good,” he said. “Maybe that would leave time for other stuff.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Other stuff? Like what?” Larry asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t know. I’m always so busy with school. Maybe once I’m done and working I’ll have time to do other stuff. I don’t know, like be in a play.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“A play?” Tiffany asked. “Aren’t you about 60 years too late for that? Or do you mean Net plays?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No, no, real plays,” he said. “Some kids do them. Seems like fun. Or marsh boating. Or playing an instrument.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "That lay there for a minute until Larry thought of something to say."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sure, a man’s got to have his fun,” he said. “I can see that. But I just worry that something like AI handler could be a ticket to nowhere. How do you get promoted from that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Huh, never thought of that,” he said, not wanting to tell him that was exactly the point. Promotion meant having to deal with the higher ups, having to believe the bullshit and be able to recite it back. He wasn’t sure he wanted that kind of attention."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, let’s think about this another way,” Tiffany said. “When you think of New Kendall, I mean the whole corporation, not just here, what do you think of it as?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t know,” he said. “Teachers say it’s the world’s largest corporation. It’s everywhere and makes everything. So I thought, OK, everywhere and everything. So seeing how the AI helps steer things, I thought I’d learn a lot about all the things that New Kendall is into. Maybe I’d find something I really like there and I could go with that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Maybe, yes. But New Kendall isn’t just the world’s biggest. It’s the world’s most powerful corporation, probably the world’s most powerful organization of any kind. Do you know why?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Because they"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’re willing to shoot anyone who gets in their way, he thought. “Because it’s everywhere?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Larry smiled. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“That’s part of it, sure. And it’s into everything, sure. But old man Robertson, he was the one who first understood that AI could keep track of all the world’s goods and services and use that knowledge to make money in new ways.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Because New Kendall always knows where there’s a supply and at what price, no matter what,” Tiffany said. “That’s where I work, in Supply Intelligence. Anything you can think of, we can find it in seconds.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And we always know what it’s selling for all around the world,” Larry said. “That’s what Demand Generation does. We partner with your mom’s group. That’s what made us the perfect couple!”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik braced for the 1,000 time they laughed at that "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“joke.” And there it was!"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I just don’t know if I’d be happy doing something like that,” Mik said. “I’m good with numbers, no prob. But I think I’d be bored.” There, he’d said it. And they looked slightly miffed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Huh, never been a problem for me,” Larry said. “But maybe you think AI is where the real action is.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, maybe,” he said, actually having no idea."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It’s not,” Larry continued, satisfied he had snapped the trap shut. “Is that what you want? To be more at the heart of things? Then you should think about Monetization. That’s what make New Kendall’s world go round.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I thought they just counted the money,” he said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“They do,” Tiffany said, “after they figure out how to make it. They put together the intel from Sup Int and Demand Gen and figure out what to buy and where to sell it to make the highest profit. For example, we might discover that there’s a bumper crop of cattle in Siberia because the spring was warm enough, early enough, to lengthen the feeding season and fatten them up. Dem Gen might find out that Korea’s soy crop didn’t do so well and they’re looking for any form of protein and willing to pay for it.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“But Korea could buy all sorts of things,” Mik protested, “and they have lots of money. Wouldn’t you want to sell it to, say, Spain, because they had such a bad drought this year and their crops failed?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Tiffany chuckled. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“New Kendall is not a charity. Spain also has tons of debt and couldn’t buy that much of the Siberian surplus. Korea can buy it all and is willing to pay 5% over market to get it and freeze it for next year, just in case.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what are the people in Spain going to eat?” he asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“That’s the genius of New Kendall,” Larry said. “We’ll locate low-cost crops and sell it to Spain and still make a profit.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So, let ‘em eat corn?” Mik asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“More like millet,” Larry said. “Beggars can’t be choosers.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And that’s the kind of stuff Monetization does?” he asked. “Figure out who to fleece and who to screw?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Mik! Why would you say that?” his mother asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Isn’t that what it is?” he asked. “I don’t know if I want to be involved in that. I’ve got nothing against Spain. Or Korea. I just want to stay dry and have three squares a day. And whatever happened to figuring out how to fix the world?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What do you think we are doing?” Tiffany asked. “We’re the only thing standing between this broken world and utter chaos.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Then we are truly fucked, Mik thought. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, I thought we were just making money so we could live better.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No need for sarcasm, young man,” Larry said. “If you have a better idea, we’re all ears.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I wish I did. But I think at least in AI I’d have some time to think about that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, it’s your life,” Tiffany said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "If only, he thought. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, I still have time to think it over. I’ll give it some thought. Meanwhile, I promised Junior I’d meet him and the guys up at the Teen Center.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Alright, just be home by 10. School night.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He walked over to the school. In the back, the gym door was open. At night, they let the kids use it to hang out. He found Junior and Manuel and his cousin Seanito."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Look who showed up,” Junior said. “Nila dump you, or she got her "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "period?"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Very funny,” he said. “Out of town. No choice but to look at your ugly face.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You want a choice? How about kissing my ass?” Junior shot back, but there was no fire in it."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You must really want some butt love,” Manny said, “looking for this guy to kiss it.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Guys, guys,” Mik said. “I got it. I ain’t been down here in awhile and you’re jealous. Let’s not waste this precious time arguing about just how true that is. I’m happy to see you after dinner with my folks, anyway. They seem to think they’re recruiters for New K "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " getting all up on me about jobs and ambition.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I hear you,” Junior said. “You know they just want to make sure you’re happy. And that you’ll have enough Kendall coin to feed their asses when they’re 55 and New K dumps them for somebody younger and better looking.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sounds like the voice of experience,” Manny said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“We’ve all had that talk,” Seanito said. “Big Sean wants me to follow him into Def. ‘I’ve blazed the trail, hijo. You just need to walk in my footsteps.’ And who’s going to scrape all the bullshit off my shoes walking in them steps?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Truth,” Mik said. “My dad thinks I should shoot for Monetization. Which I finally found out what they do.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Do tell,” Junior said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Turns out they’re the ones who figure out who’s going to get the worst screwing, as far as squeezing people for coin.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh yeah, my dad told me the same,” Seanito said. “The way he tells it, Sec finds out where the toilet paper is stored, Def goes and steals it, and Money sends texts to all the people on the shitter letting them know how they can get fresh toilet paper for only twice the normal price.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They all laughed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“But seriously, what are you guys thinking about doing?” Mik asked, curious. And no one had any more idea than he did."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Maybe it don’t matter anyway,” Junior said. “Robertson and his guys call the shots. We’re just the drones making it all happen. Red drone, blue drone, what’s the dif?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You know they’re going to tell you?” Seanito said. “They’ll sit us down in a few weeks and tell us what the AI recommends. My dad says they give you three choices. They say you can do anything else, but if you don’t pick one of those three, you might get a pretty tough welcome wherever you go. They’ll see you as dead wood from the start, you’ll always have to prove that the AI was wrong. You’ll always be blamed when things don’t go right.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, toss a three-sided coin, Mik,” Manny advised. “Don’t stress about it. Whatever, you’ll get high ground, four walls and three squares. And a free subscription to Kendall Entertainment Network.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik let it go. He could see they weren"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t too happy but didn’t want to admit there was nothing they could do about it."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::2>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik talks with his parents about jobs he might take after graduating. He learns more about what NK is really about and what is choices might really be."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Later, he goes out with the old gang. They all have had this talk, and they recount some of how it went."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He sees that no one is happy, but most are just accepting it. Not everyone though. He"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s intrigued by that, although not certain what to do about it."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He realizes that stay or leave, he has to have a cover story. He"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’ll have to pretend to be choosing between a couple of things just to avoid scrutiny."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
