      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "School scene",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>The caf was buzzing. Today was the day that they called you in and told you the official recommendations of New Kendall Corporation for your future employment "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " The List. The AI had spoken and today you were to listen to its three magic choices for the rest of your life. Junior had already gotten his. He looked surprised."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what did the Wizard of Oz have to say?” Mik asked. “Anything good?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t know, I’m still trying to figure that out,” Junior said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, what were your three choices?” Mik asked. “Don’t be shy.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“That’s the thing. They didn’t even give me three,” he said. “Just one. And I wasn’t expecting it.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“They want me to study Bahasa.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What the fuck is that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It’s what they speak in Indonesia. They said they need more people who speak their language because they want to expand operations there and I’d be a good candidate.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Why you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Junior looked embarassed. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, you know…”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No!’ Mik exclaimed. “Just because you’re Asian?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Junior nodded. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And my family came from the Phillipines, not Indonesia. Thirty years ago. I’ve never even been to Asia. I told them that, but you know what they said?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Can’t even imagine.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“’Close enough.’ Can you fucking believe that? They want me to learn the language and then be an interpreter for them.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Here?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No they want me to learn it here but then move there,” Junior said. “You know what it felt like? Like they were saying ‘Go back to where you came from’ only they didn’t even have that right.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“That’s messed up,” Mik said. “I’ve never heard of anything like that. Something must be messed up over there. What are you going to do?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What can I do?” Junior said. “You heard what Seanito said. Mess with them and you’ll never be right. Always be working with people who don’t want you.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Maybe. Who knows if Big Sean really has it right. But I could see it’s a big risk. What do you think your folks will say.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No idea,” Junior said. “I’m still trying to figure out how to tell them. They wanted me to go for Monetization, just like your folks. All the parents think Monetization is like winning the lottery. I hope they don’t blame me, like I did something wrong.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Or maybe you did something right. Sounds like they think you can handle crises. Like the Alewife bridge.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, fuck, I hadn’t thought of that. You’re right! They must have seen that as a little test "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " we didn’t freak out, we didn’t rat them out to Everywhere, we kept our mouths shut even here in New Kendall. ‘We can trust that kid.’ Now I wish I had said something.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Then they’d be recommending you for maintenance. Sewer repair specialist, fourth class. So count your blessings, I guess.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It still feels like I’ve landed in the shit anyway.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They picked over their soy chili in silence. Mik felt bad for Junior, which gave way to feeling anxious about his session with The List adviser, which would be right after lunch. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "*****<!$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>Mik sat on a bench in the hallway, along with a handful of other kids. No one talked. They were just trying to keep it together at this point and desparately wanted not to show too much emotion to other kids. The door opened and a girl from his math class walked out. She had a little smile on her face "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " not too bad, it said. A hand waived him in from inside, a disembodied voice said "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Mik.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He walked in to see a man he had never met sitting behind a desk."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Ferd Cragen,” the man said, as if that explained everything. “Have a seat.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Cragen made a show of finding Mik"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s record on his puter, as if it were some incredible feat of detective work."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Ah, here we are. OK, so we have our results. Huh, interesting. It suggests marketing, logistics, or AI interfacer. What do you think of that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, that’s great,” Mik said, relieved that none of them were his parents’ favorites. “Do I have to tell you now?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No, not at all. In fact, these are just suggestions and we need to talk about them. It’s actually an unusual combination "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " only 3% of students got the same 3 choices. But hey, it’s a new century ahead and we need to walk some new paths, eh? Tell me what you think about them, what interests you about them.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "This felt like a trap, so he paused, trying to keep his face thoughtful. He wouldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t reveal his cards totally. “Well, I can see why they choose that for me. I’m usually good with numbers and logic, so that explains marketing and logistics. And I’m good at patterns, too, so that must be why they suggested AI interfacer.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Patterns, eh?” Cragen said quizically. “I’m not sure I see what you’re getting at.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, the AI uses algorithms to analyze and decide stuff. Algorithms are based on patterns "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " if this, then that. My mind kind of works like that, too, at least that’s what some of my teachers have told me. Sometimes AIs don’t see things that don’t belong in the pattern, things a person could see. A person like me. It’s a challenge "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " it’s basically a “what doesn’t belong” or “what’s wrong with this picture” sort of thing. I enjoy that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“OK, that’s a novel way to look at it, but I see where you’re coming from. It’s not just statistics to you, it’s a picture.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sort of.” He could see Cragen was trying to goad him into saying he was smarter than the AI. “I mean the AI works with stats and all sorts of analyses that are way beyond me. I’m just saying when it spits out its result, I tend to see a pattern that it’s created. And you can go from there, to ask if that pattern is useful or matches everyday experience. Like I saw the pattern in the three choices the AI is giving me. Maybe it’s an odd combo "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " you would know that of course. But to me, I could see the logic, the pattern.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, apparently the AI could see that in you, too,” Cragen said in an overly cheery voice. “It sounds like you’re most enthusiastic about the AI interface job. Tell me how you see that working in, say, 2110.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Again with the new century, Mik thought. Give it a rest!"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Gee, I hadn’t thought about that too much,” Mik said. “But I know that some of the interfacers become AI engineers, getting deeper into the code and helping improve it.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yet you’re not rated here for software engineer.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“True. I know I would have to study more on that. I could learn on the job.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Perhaps,” Cragen said. “The trend now, though, is to have the AI write its own code.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "This was news to him. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what would be the next step up from AI interfacer?” Mik asked. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Still evolving. But if I had to guess, it would be human engineering.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik hadn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t heard that phrase before. “Oh, interesting. We didn’t learn about that yet in school, What’s it about?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It’s about engineering processes and policies and rules that make it more likely that people will do the right thing without even having to think too hard about it. That’s what the next century is going to be all about. Right now, for example, we’re working with fishing villages in Asia to improve their productivity. In Hum Eng, they’re looking at what incentives are most attractive to the those people: money, goods, security, or something they discover that wasn’t apparent. Or it might be disincentives: fines for not making quotas and so on. And then the AIs can do all the crunching to come up with the amounts of money or quotas or whatever that will be most effective.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Fascinating. Sure, I could see myself doing that in a few years.” A few hundred years, he thought. He couldn’t wait for this to be over."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What attracts you to it?” "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Freakin"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’ New Kendall, Mik thought. They never just take yes for an answer. It has to be yes for the right reason, meaning their reason. Tread carefully, he thought. “It’s another pattern, isn’t it? Those fishing people, their life has patterns, too. It would be fun to figure out what makes them go.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " Mik sensed he had found an answer that was neither what Cragen wanted to hear nor one he could really argue against. Cragen seemed stuck on pause for a minute."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Okay,” Cragen said. “I’ve noted that here. We’ll let the people in AI interface know that. If you decide to go that route, they can mentor you toward that. Do you want to choose now?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Could I take some time? Like to talk to my folks, make sure for myself.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Absolutely. We’ll need your answer by the end of the month. And of course, we’re always here to help.  I’ve sent my info to your Voice, should you want to talk further. Otherwise, we’re done here.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And with that, he ushered Mik out, passing the next lamb to slaughter on the way."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Have to get back to job selection somehow.  This scene should involve all the kids."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
