    {
      "id": 12,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 1,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 11,
      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "The kids compare notes",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>Mik was almost feeling relieved. At least AI interfacer was something he wouldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t hate. That much. He was dying to find out what his friends got. Everyone would be at The Dive, their name for Hot Joes,  coffee bar that mostly catered to low-level office clerks from the New Kendall offices. That was the beauty of The Dive "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " they wouldn’t have to see any of the other kids from school. And the regulars there couldn’t care less what they were talking about."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Junior and Seanito had already grabbed the big table in the back corner. They looked neither crushed nor celebratory."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Hey,” Mik said. “How’d it go?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Grand,” Junior said. “I’m going to be Ken Robertson’s new assistant. Job comes with a penthouse apartment.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And it all works out,” Seanito said, “’cause I’m going to be the bodyguard/chauffeur. That way I get to use the limo on my own time. Girls love that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So Junior, you got logistics, and Seanito, you got maintenance, right?” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wiseguy. Yes, I did get logistics, but also marketing and product development,” Junior said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And no, I didn’t get maintenance,” Seanito said. “New Kendall is very committed to new opportunities for people from non-European backgrounds, didn’t you know that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They all laughed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Seriously, I got Def, so my dad will be happy,” Seanito said. “But I also got demographic analyst and infrastructure planner.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wow, we have infrastructure planners?” Mik said. “Who knew?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, that’s the most interesting one to me,” Seanito said. “Maybe I could actually do some good. New roads, housing, that sort of thing.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Somebody has to figure out how to make underwater sleeping bags,” Junior said. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad,” Seanito said. “But enough about me. What’s your gig, Mik?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, I got marketing and logistics, too, like Junior. No offense, not interested.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No worries, me neither,” Junior said. “What was your third?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“That was the good news "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " AI interfacer,” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Really? You want to talk to puters all day?” Seanito asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“More than I want to talk to corpos, I’m pretty sure,” Mik said. “So I’m not too bummed out. Was your interview weird?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You mean, are we in New Kendall?” Junior asked. “But specifically, what was weird?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik saw Nila out of the corner of his eye, headed there way."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Hey,” she said, slumping down into the chair. She waved toward the server, who came over, having nothing else to do."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Can I get a beer?” she asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No,” he said. “Not until after 4. You know the rules. ‘Clear minds make clear choices at work and school.’”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, everything’s too clear already,” Nila said. “But I don’t want you to get in trouble., You guys all want coffee?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They nodded."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Four white coffees then,” Nila said. The server went away. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So?” Mik asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So, I’m fucked,” Nila said. “Sec, monetization or surveillance.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wow, you won the lottery,” Seanito said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, why are you so bummed,” Junior said. “My parents would die for me to have that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“We’re all lifers here,” Nila said. “But we all don’t have to give a shit. Like all these guys sitting around us. They go to work, they go home, they get their three squares and their dry feet. They kiss their partner, fuck enough to get their one kid, and then keep the kid out of too much trouble. No one cares what they think, they don’t have to make a big show of how grateful they are. All of that "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " I’d rather have all of that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I’m with you on that,” Mik said. “That’s why I’m not too bummed about AI interfacer "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " I can do that without having to be all gung ho and rah rah.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“A little enthusiasm never killed anyone,” Seanito said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, there were those fugees that tried to cross the river,” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad,” Junior said. “But they were desperate. I just want to have two feet out of the water. If I have to show a little enthusiasm to have dry feet, I might make that move. Seems dumb not to.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Junior seemed annoyed. Mik wondered if Nila was about to snap his head off, but she softened."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I get that. I know I have it lucky, my mom’s a corpo and all,” Nila said. “But a little enthusiasm is worse than none with those guys. You have to be all in with them. They test you all the time.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I got a taste of that,” Mik said. “Cragen, the guy who interviewed me, he kept wanting to know what I want to do in five or ten years. How the hell would I know? I didn’t know what to say and it felt like there was definitely a wrong answer, even if I didn’t know what it was.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what did you say?” Nila asked."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Nothing. I got him to talk instead. He answered the question for me and I just nodded and said, yeah, that sounds interesting.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Smart,” Nila said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, I guess we all have some hard choices to make,” Junior said. “Like are we going to put sugar in our coffee?” "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The server put four mugs down. They drank and talked about the new stream from Smiling Cloud, the band they all liked. In the new stream, there was one very quick scene where they band was dressed in short green pants and orange tunics. Nila thought they were giving a nod to some rebel group in the UK. Junior thought it was the colors of their favorite footie team. Neither Mik nor Seanito had noticed. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Hey, Nila, I didn’t mean to come down so hard on you,” Junior said. “I guess I was pissed because you burst my bnbble a little. Truth is, I don’t know why I should give a shit. It’s not like New Kendall is going to make the world better. If I ever have a kid, they’ll probably have it even worse. And their kids. Just sometimes, I have to pretend it matters.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I hear you,” Nila said. “I’m not saying your a fool to feel that way. Who doesn’t want to hope for the best? I just feel they’re using that to make fools of us. It pisses me off. But I know we all have to do what we all have to do.” "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They had finished their coffee by the time they decided no one had any idea what it meant. They paid their bill and started to leave. Nila turned away from Junior and Seanito toward Mik."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Walk with me?” Nila asked Mik."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sure,” Mik said. “Hey guys, see you later, OK? And glad you guys got something you liked.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, you too,” Junior said. And he Seanito headed down toward the gym."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wow, I thought you and Junior were going to duke it out there for a minute,” Mik said when they were out of earshot."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah for a minute I thought so too,” Nila. “But he’s alright. Look, I know I’m a spoiled corpo brat. What can I do about it?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Nothing,” Mik agreed. “But I was glad you didn’t snap back at him. And I think he appreciated it, too. There’s no sense in us all falling on each other because of New Kendall.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Nila nodded. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’m too depressed to fight with my friends, anyway. I’m so fucked.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I heard you say that. Because you got Sec?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, but not just that. Don’t you see what’s going on?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Not sure I know what you mean,” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“My mom’s wired me up. Sec, monetization, surveillance. Junior and Seanito are not wrong "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " those are the golden tickets around here. To a lifetime in the upper echelons of New Kendall. They’ve sent me a message "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " you’re one of the elite.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Huh, hadn’t thought of it that way. And you don’t want to be, I get that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And it’s worse. My mom hit me on my Voice right after the meeting. She’s so proud, nyak, nyak. She’s practically packed my bags for Security boot camp.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What if you picked monetization or surveillance? Would that be better?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No, I’d just have to push harder to make an impression. My mom’s pull with them isn’t so strong. Although I’m starting to wonder if maybe Kenny boy wasn’t in on this, too.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Mik was startled. Why would Robertson care about her? This was when she annoyed him, with her penchant for dramatics."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What if you didn’t make an impression? What if you did demand surveillance and just put in your time and didn’t crush it?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You can’t half step it in those jobs. They’d give me a couple of stern talkings and then ship me off to wash dishes in a mining camp. It happened to someone my mom worked with "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " they make examples out of people who are ‘let into the tent and then just piss in the corner.’ That’s how they see it.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what are you going to do?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sneak a few of my mom’s chewies and sleep for a week.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sounds like plan,” he laughed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“But what about you? That interview sounded creepy.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It was. I’ve never met that guy before. Ferd Cragen.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, no! He’s a super creep. Remember little Annie Nova?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I do. Very nervous, anxious all the time. Whatever happened to her?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Cragen used to be a head doc. He treated her. No idea for what, all hush hush. But she opened up to me "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " I guess I didn’t know I was an empath back then. She told him she was having all these problems. You now what he told her? It was all her fault, she was ungrateful, needed to look deep into her soul and straighten out and fly right, all that bullshit. I didn’t know what to say, but it sure sounded like bullshit. A week later, she topped herself.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No! I knew there was something off about him.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, don’t listen to a word he says.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I didn’t. But I’m not feeling as trapped as you. This AI interfacer, I actually like doing that. And I can half-step it, as you say, all the way to the end. Nobody really cares.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Maybe, maybe not,” she said. “Shit happens around here, and nobody asks you your opinion. But doesn’t it feel sad? Our whole life in front of us, and we’re trying to find a way to do the least we can?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And survive,” he said. “Let’s not forget that part. Not everyone can say that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad,” she said. “And I just don’t know if I can stand being part of making that worse.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, it’s a bitch. Dammed either way. What are we going to do?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Besides get wasted? I don’t know. Well, at least you can kiss me.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And he did. For a few seconds, neither of them cared about the future. And then she ran up the path to her building and disappeared."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
