    {
      "id": 14,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 1,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 13,
      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "Des uncovers attack plan",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>Ever since Des had told him how the waveform had harmonies that might be useful, Raefe had been trying to train himself to find them. At first, he wondered if Des had been mistaken. No matter how he tried, he could not find feel any minds other than in the giant broad rainbow of thoughts he always heard. Then one day he had been sitting on a bench on Cambridge Common when a young woman walked by with a baby in a stroller. He thought, that baby is going to cry and seconds later it did."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And then he thought, mom"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s going to give the baby a monkey and laughed. What an odd thing to think! And then the woman pulled a stuffed animal out of the large bag handing on the stroller and handed it to the baby. It was a toy monkey. The baby stopped crying."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "This must be it, he thought. I sensed some communication between them. Do mothers and babies have their own lane in the waveform? He stared away from the pair so they wouldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t notice him. He closed his eyes and slowed his breathing. He could hear the mother’s mind in all the usual ways but now he could hear her mind wane, almost pause and then…there it was! She had shifted her thoughts in the waveform to the baby’s frequency or wavelength or whatever it was. Just for a few seconds and then she was back. He shut out everything but her mind, being careful not to touch it enough to alarm her. And he saw how she did it, unthinkingly. It was a bit like squinting, a bit like changing your focus from far to near."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The next time she did it, he was able to mimic her. And then he heard it, the baby"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s mind. It was a note of contentment. The mother smiled and went back to her previous thoughts.  Did all mother’s do that? All babies? He had to tell Des. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Des was always easy to find. No one on Earth had their mind in as many places as him at one time, and no one had quite his mental signature."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’ve done it,” Raefe said. “What you explained to me.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wow! What’s it like?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Just starting out. Follow me now.” And Raefe replayed his memory of the mother and child."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, that’s interesting!”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yes, much more here than just a back channel, eh? Let’s talk more about that when it’s safe. Do you think we can try to have this conversation there?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And he felt Des make that switch that the mother had. And Raefe followed and he still felt Des"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s mind. Nothing was really different, it just felt a bit odd, like singing a note that was at the edge of your range."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It’s quieter here,” Des said. “Like we have the room to ourself. Almost "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " I can hear occasional blips from the child.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“It’s really just a baby "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " probably can’t even talk yet.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’ve actually never tangled with a baby,” Des said. “I’ll have to ask Anti if she does with her kids.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“There’s so much the Guardians never told us, it makes you wonder how much more we don’t know about entangling. But let’s put that aside for the moment. I’m anxious to hear what you’ve learned about our old sparring partners.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Still digging, but so far, it’s not good. They’re definitely planning something and soon. I think they want to test their abilities on more than just a prisoner in a chair. And I think that means that they will try an action somewhere nearby.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“We’re as near as it gets to them,” Raefe said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I agree and I think you may be in danger,” Des said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Can you find out more?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yes, but so can you,” Des said. “But maybe you shouldn’t "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " they know your mind. Who else is adept in your circle? Who you can trust?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Tosh, for sure,” Raefe said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Of course,” Des said. “We should ask him if he’s willing to scout them. It’s not without risk.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’m happy to ask him. I’m sure he’ll say yes. But I don’t know if I can explain what he should be looking for. I can, however, show him how to tangle like this.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I can tell him what to look for. Tell him to find me when he’s ready. He’ll need help, too. Are there three or four people who are safe to train for this?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yes, for sure. But how can we prepare ourselves? Are we talking about picking up and moving? Fighting back somehow? Figuring out ways to protect ourselves?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Might be moving at first, but I don’t think for long. Once they deploy, I feel like we’ll probably be able to figure out how to defuse their attack. Like I said when we talked before, they don’t really get what they’re doing. People here are working on counter measures, too. We just need to buy time.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Okay. I always have a bag packed. Force of habit. Find me this way, though. Don’t hesitate, day or night. And think about how we want to use these new channels. Who else? Mom, Mari, of course, and now Tosh. But who else?<!$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
