    {
      "id": 15,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 1,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 14,
      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "Nila leaves",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>The spring air felt good to Nila. The winter had mostly hovered in the 40s but the frequent storms had made it cold and raw. In a month or two, the swampy weather would take hold. But for now, it was just on the warm side and the sun felt good on her face. The Torn Nets were in her ears, the nasal twang and infectious tuned drums of Filipino reggae adding to the smile on her face. She wondered if the Secs understood the Nets words. All those songs about fish swimming free "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " did they get that we were the fish?"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "That"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s what was so exhausting about New K. You could never just relax and enjoy yourself. Was someone watching, listening? And what were they looking for? And did it matter? Well, she wasn’t going to let them spoil her afternoon. Mik would be here soon and hang out and just not worry about it all."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And there he was, his gangly self, his messy hair, and those soulful eyes. Maybe it wasn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t forever, but she did like him."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oye, amiga,” he said. “How are you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Loving this weather,” she said. “You want to grab a java at Mo’s? We could sit outside.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They walked a few blocks from Mass Ave to Mohammed"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s Coffee and Cake, which had the benefit of having neither other kids or New K brass as frequent visitors. Some of the teachers went there, but they never talked to you off hours anyway."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So what you been up to?” Mik asked after they had gotten their coffees."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, this and that. They’ve been screening old vids at Modern Times. We watched one about these enactors, well actors back then, who are travelling around doing plays after this plague kills off most of the world.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yikes, that sounds grim,” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“The plague, yeah. They didn’t have all the drugs we have now, so they couldn’t fix it. But otherwise, it reminded me of that virus in 2091.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, that sucked. Did you get that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yup. Why do you think I’m a year older than everyone else? I was sick for half a year. My mom says I could have died.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wow, I didn’t realize that. You weren’t here then, were you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No, Val got posted to Finland, of all places. Pretty quiet up there, just a lot of swamp, mostly. But then it turned out there are these biker gangs that travel across the old Arctic lands, smuggling shit. Mostly drugs. The go from Siberia all the way to Norway. On their way through Finland, they managed to pass the virus on and before anyone knew it, it was everywhere. My mom claims that New K saved my life, that they air-dropped in experimental drugs before everyone else got them.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What was it like? When you had the virus.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t remember the first part. I was delirious, in a dream for weeks. I guess I had a really high fever. After that, I just felt so weak. I used to be chubby, you know. I lost 40 lbs. I’m still too skinny. But they made me stay inside for weeks after I was better. That’s when I first discovered I liked old vids. I had nothing else to do. They wouldn’t let any other kids near me.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So you learned to be on your own. I always wondered how you were so ‘I don’t give a fuck’ about what other kids thought about you.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’m not actually. I just don’t have a choice. My mom was very insistent that I never tell anyone about it when we moved back. Some people think once you are infected, you’ll always be infectious. Don’t worry, it’s bullshit. But people believe a lot of bullshit. Anyway, I wasn’t trying to be standoffish. I just was. I hadn’t talked to anyone in months, wasn’t up on the latest whatever. Maybe if I’d said, hey, I’ve been locked up for 6 months, fill me in, it would have been different. But everyone assumed I just thought I was too cool to like what they liked.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Not that you would like it just because they did,” Mik pointed out."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, fair enough,” she said. “But all this New K team spirit, it’s mostly a mirage to me. But hey, I don’t really like to dwell on that time. So what’s up with you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He told her about the trip to mall with his dad."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“At the end, he got a little teary with me. Like he was hoping we would be some father/son Demand Gen team. I guess I never thought it meant that much to him.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, my mom’s the same way.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And then he started in on the whole new century thing. Like the calendar is going to save us.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad,” she said. “But I bet your dad doesn’t really understand what New K means by the new century. He probably just takes it at face value, you know, things are going to turn around get better.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Delusional,” Mik said."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Indeed,” Nila said. “But I heard what Rob’s Junior said about it, and it’s not just rah-rah. It’s going to be nasty. They’re going for world domination.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“My folks think New K already dominates the world. They think New K is the most powerful organization in the world.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Maybe,” Nila said. “But it’s a big world and they don’t just want to be the most powerful. They want to be powerful enough to control most of the world, which they’re not. That’s what the new century means to them.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I hadn’t thought of it quite that way,” Mik admitted. “Makes me even more glad I’m not going into Demand Gen.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Have you decided yet?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, I’m gonna give AI a try. You?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Nila could see the hesitation on his face, like he wasn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t sure he wanted to know."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Got a few days yet. I want to go, I’ll be honest. You’re just about the only reason I would stay.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Thanks, I guess,” Mik said. “I mean, that would be great. But I don’t want you to be unhappy.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Well, that makes two of us,’ she said, smiling to reassure him."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What if you crossed the river? Maybe you could do something with, you know, your friend over there? Maybe I could sneak over there and see you.” "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s a sweet kid, she thought. “You know, I hadn’t considered that. I’m going to think that one through. Like I said, still a few days to work things out.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She downed the rest of her coffee and they got up to go for a walk up toward the park.<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "* * * * *<!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She had to admit, she hadn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t really thought about just crossing the river. All of her plans had been to go far away. Hudson’s Bay, maybe. You heard that there were all sorts of new farms and things up there, a new world to build. And no New K. Yet."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She went up on the roof of her building to clear her head. She looked south toward Cambridge and Boston beyond. From here, Cambridge looked like anywhere else around New Kendall. Rivers, marshes, fields, clusters of homes, clusters of ruins, all connected by half-broken roads filled with mostly with bikes and the occasional truck."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Her mind was calm now, She let the waveform wash over her, hearing bits and pieces of so many minds. In the stress of the last weeks, her ability to entangle seemed to have taken a leap "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " all those minds seemed more vivid, more detailed now. She remembered what Raefe"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s felt like and there it was."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Hey,” she said. “I was hoping we could talk.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Sure,” he said. “You feel…complicated. Is everything OK?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yes and no. The List came out. You know about that?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, sure. You’re worried about your choice?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“They’ve got me boxed in. My folks have made sure I’m fast-tracked for the inner circle. I don’t think I can do that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You’re not alone there. Year by year, they lose more people like you.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I kind of had that sense. And I was wondering…”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wait! Where are you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She let him see through her eyes. She could feel that his mind was also occupied with others, with voices she couldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t hear."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I can’t explain, but you’re in danger. Go, now, don’t stop until you get to the place we met. Someone will come for you.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "And he was gone. She couldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t feel him anymore. For a second, she tried to scan for anyone nearby, but nothing. There was a ladder that went down two floors to another roof, where the air conditioning was. There was a door there that went down a back stairway. She didn’t know what Raefe had felt, but she had an idea that if she stopped, she would never be free again. She ran all the way down, and out, and kept running.<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "*****<!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Raefe talked to Tosh about saving Nila. They knew that some of the Norcamb bunch had ways to sneak in to New Kendall. But could they get all the way to the Nila"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s hiding place? They agreed Tosh would bike up to the Norcamb settlement and see if they could help. He was back in an hour, smiling."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“They’ll have her back here before dark. ‘Piece of pie’ they said. Cheeky lot!”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Nothing wrong with that!” Raefe said. “I’m just glad we can get her out.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Raefe alerts Nila to the danger she"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s in. Nila decides now’s the time to get outside NK’s reach. Hudson Bay awaits."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She and Mik talk it through one more time. He"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s still ambivalent, afraid of winding up starving to death in some far away place he’s never even seen on the net."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "They agree to keep in touch, tangling if they can. They leave heartbroken but maybe it"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’s for the best?"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
