    {
      "id": 17,
      "lineId": 1,
      "beatId": 1,
      "bookId": 1,
      "positionWithinLine": 16,
      "positionInBeat": 0,
      "title": "Mik meets Ines",
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<$Scr_Ps::0>It was Decision Day and he had made his. School let out early so they could all celebrate. He waved off Junior and Seanito. He wasn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t in the mood. He hadn’t seen Nila since coffee at Mo’s. Maybe she had actually done it and run away. He hoped she was OK, but he was angry at her and sad for both of them, all balled up together."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "His feet pulled him inexorably toward the Broadway Bridge. That was the place where everything had started to really come apart for him. It was just a block long piece of road over a small, occasionally raging, swollen river. Today, though, it was calm. There weren"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t even guards at the bridge. But the gates were down, the cameras on and they would be here in seconds if anyone tried to cross into New K."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He still couldn"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "’t figure out why people were killed over this little stream. It looked pretty today, green trees and some early spring flowers along the banks. He could see people on the other side, but they paid no attention to him. I’ll bet New K is way more obsessed with them than they are with us, he thought. They’re just living life."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Too bad your masters can’t see that way,” a woman said from behind and he turned around. She was standing in a doorway, hard to see unless you were right where he was. She looked familiar."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“We almost met once. I come to your school with Raefe Epstein Miller. I’m Ines.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He remembered her, walking down the street with Raefe and some other people the day after the attack at this bridge."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You were the one trying to cross with the zip line, weren’t you?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yes.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I was there, you know. They make us kids help watch during the storm. Me and another kid, we were over there.” He pointed to the building where he and Junior had watched that night. “I thought they were going to kill us to shut us up. Cleaning up loose ends, you know? It was outrageous what they did to you.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "She nodded. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So everyone over here isn’t an animal. REM, he preach that. I don’t always believe it. But here you are.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What are you doing here? How did you get in?” Suddenly he wondered if he was going to be a human sacrifice for New Kendall’s sins."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Relax, you’re safe, Raefe sent me.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh. Why?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“He wants you to know Nila is safe. She had to leave quick time. The Secs were going to swoop her away.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“What? Why? She’s just a rebellious kid.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“They learn she tangles.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“And they were going to arrest for that? She can’t be the only one.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad! But maybe the only one who tangles with REM himself. They were, how can we say, concerned. I think you know they get dangerous when they’re concerned. Maybe not just arrest her either.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Oh, man. It’s my fault. She was trying to sort out what to do. We have to pick jobs and she was being squeezed into ones she hated and I told her, maybe she could live on your side and we could still, well…”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Ah, you care for her. She must care for you, because she strong that someone had to let you know  she’s OK and not to worry. So I don’t think she blames you, either.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Where is she?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t know. I don’t want to know. This shit is getting real again. The Secs have some tanglers, and they’re coming after tanglers they don’t like, which is everyone else.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“So you’re with Everywhere?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“No, not exactly. I can tangle, but I ain’t sold on the whole one big tangled up human race. Some people I definitely don’t want to share my thoughts with, and want to be in their minds even less. You seem OK, though. But to answer, I’m not with Everywhere. I’m a Norcamb "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " you know all those people out rough up on this end? We rub shoulders with Everywhere a lot. Raefe knows I have ways of slipping in and out of New K unnoticed and his people asked if I would talk to you. I owed him for negotiating with New K over the killings. I would have just got us all killed if it weren’t for him.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Nila really digs him. I don’t know what to think. Some days I don’t even know whether to think.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Ines laughed. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad! So what are you going to be when you grow up?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "He told her about choosing AI interfacer and why."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Trying to keep your head down. Your shoes, smart move. No need to shame yourself.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Thanks. It just feels lame.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Be lame if you told me how cool it was. You see all that muck and marsh out there? Fastest person in the world no faster than me running across that.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Not sure I follow.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“The wet world made everyone lame. No prize for first, only for finishing. Go easy, stay easy.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Says the woman who hung on a zipline over raging waters to get an old truck across the river.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“You the sharp one. Yeah, no one said I had any sense. But I grew up in the shit. You just smell it from over here. Different to walk in it every day.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Verdad. But I’m not sure they’ll let me stay out of it. I’m finding out there’s a lot they don’t tell you in school.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Wouldn’t know. Never been. But yeah, New K lies about everything, in case you were wondering.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Was coming around to that point of view. Nila, actually, helped me see a lot of that. But I’m not as brave as her. Or you. I’m just trying, like you say, to keep my head down. Maybe sometimes, though, I want to poke it up and make a difference.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’ll tell the man. That’s Raefe’s territory, organizing shit. I’m just trying to keep my dad alive and the people around me dry. But REM, he always thinking about bringing people into the fight, even just a little.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I don’t know how I can help, but I would like to know. Good to have options. And thanks for bringing the news. I miss her already. But I guess I knew this was going to happen, her leaving. At least she’s safe.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Yeah, New Kendall can’t grab her up now. She’ll hear about our talk, one way or another. So keep thinking of her. She don’t tangle great yet, but she might get to where she can find you from wherever she’s going. Maybe you tangle a bit?”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Not really. I think I’m easy to read when I’m relaxed around someone I trust. But I got no way to find them, no way to scan.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“Interesting. Probably a lot of people like you. That’s one thing Raefe didn’t count on "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "—"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": " maybe everyone can’t tangle. Or don’t want to.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“I’d love to. I just can’t. But yeah, if Nila can reach out, that would be great. I’m not mad at her for leaving. I just miss her.”"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "“We all got a lot of people we miss. I should go now.” She darted off along the river bank, away from the bridge. She disappeared into a stand of trees and then he couldn’t see her at all."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<!$Scr_Ps::0>"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
